{"_id":"GodUnderMine","name":"The God Under the Mine","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/mouth-teeth-long-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":6,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a creature as old as the world, trapped beneath the bedrock","Millennia of inactivity have made me catatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up","Only pain can stir me even slightly"],"gifts":[{"name":"The Head of the God","description":"Only the enormous head of the God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be obtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits a loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check can avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the God's fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the next action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When reduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to fully regenerate in the following Scene."}],"background":"An ancient god-like creature, a huge pig-like being embedded in the rock below Whitehaven. It has been trapped for millennia, and its long inactivity has made it catatonic - there is nothing that can truly wake it. Only pain can stir it slightly. The mine collapse caused by its stirring left Arthur Browne trapped underground, where he discovered the God's head protruding from the north wall of a natural cave. Arthur found that the God's flesh regenerates quickly and confers incredible powers when eaten, including the ability to transform into monstrous pig-headed forms. The God's flesh is now being distributed by Frank Browne through the slaughterhouse, mixed with common meat, creating an army of Pig Heads to wage war against Bardolf Greed."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"source-of-power","location":"cave-beneath-mine","status":"catatonic-regenerating"}}